 A 16-year-old boy has been nabbed for the murder of a 14-year-old boy in Claremont, in Joburg. This is after he pulled out a stolen gun and allegedly shot the 14-year-old boy dead. According to the cops it is alleged that the teenagers were in the same apartment when the suspect who was carrying a firearm pulled the trigger and the bullet hit the deceased. Police spokesman, Captain Mavela Masondo said in a statement, “Preliminary investigation revealed that the firearm used was stolen in Moffatview last month and police managed to trace and arrest a 19-year-old that is alleged to be responsible for the theft of firearm.” Masondo said the teenager will appear in the Joburg Magistrate court tomorrow. (Monday) In the cop’s mission to remove illegal firearms that are in circulation, Masondo said two suspects were arrested in Diepsloot after they were found in possession of unlicensed firearms. “These firearms were recovered through the tip-off from the community and when police were conducting a stop and search.”         